  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: 1.9.13-unstable\r\nOS & Version: Windows 10\r\nCommit hash : 510b6f9\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nAccording to the [LES specification](https://github.com/ethereum/devp2p/blob/master/caps/les.md), the CHT sections are divided into sections of 32768, such that \r\n\r\n> CHT[i] containing data for blocks 0..i * 32768-1\r\n> header number N (where N < i * 32768)\r\n\r\nIn the ropsten trusted checkpoint, the sectionIndex is 223, so the highest numbered block in that section should be 234 * 32768 - 1 = 7667711. \r\n \r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nThe SectionHead hash stored with section 234 in the checkpoint, is for block number 7700479.\r\nThis seems consistent with an off by one error in either the application or documentation.\r\n\r\ne.g.\r\n> CHT[i] containing data for block 0..(i + 1) * 32768 - 1\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\n1. `geth --ropsten --syncmode light --verbosity 4`\r\n2. View logs requesting CHT 234, block 7700479\r\n\r\nedit: updated block and cht numbers to match the commit hash referenced.",
